    transliteration: 'yayā tu dharmakāmārthāndhṛtyā dhārayate\'rjuna | prasaṅgena phalākāṅkṣī dhṛtiḥ sā pārtha rājasī ||',
    englishTranslation: 'But that fortitude by which one holds on to dharma, pleasure, and wealth, O Arjuna, with attachment and desire for the fruits — that fortitude, O Partha, is rajasic.',
